Jefferson Street, east side, north from Water, to Cherry Streets, showing the Roe Boarding, Sale and Exchange Stable, which bears No's. 436-454 Water Street (right).

Jefferson Street, east side, north from and including Water Street. The block from Water to Cherry Streets is a clearance created by the demolition of a 4-story building which formerly stood there, and is being used as an automobile parking ground.

March 22, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
